==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Halter
<hw>Halt"er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who halts
or limps; a cripple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Halter
<hw>Hal"ter</hw> <pr>(h⟦add⟧l"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>halter</ets>, <ets>helter</ets>, <ets>helfter</ets>, AS.
<ets>h⟦ae⟧lftre</ets>; akin to G. <ets>halfter</ets>, D.
<ets>halfter</ets>, <ets>halster</ets>, and also to E. <ets>helve</ets>.
See <er>Helve</er>.]</ety> <def>A strong strap or cord.</def>
<specif>Especially:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A rope or strap, with or
without a headstall, for leading or tying a horse.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A rope for hanging malefactors; a noose.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No man e'er felt the <qex>halter</qex> draw⟦br⟧
With good opinion of the law.</q> <rj><qau>Trumbull.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Halter
<hw>Hal"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Haltered</conjf> <pr>(-t⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Haltering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To tie by the neck
with a rope, strap, or halter; to put a halter on; to subject to a
hangman's halter.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>haltered</xex> neck.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halteres</ent>⟦br⟧
